<h2 id="overview">FieldEdge vs ServiceTitan: The Mid-Market Battleground</h2>

<p>Both FieldEdge and ServiceTitan target HVAC companies with 10+ technicians, but they serve different segments of the growing contractor market. After analyzing pricing data from 150+ HVAC shops and conducting interviews with users of both platforms, here's the reality: FieldEdge positions itself as the "enterprise-lite" solution at $150-200 per user monthly, while ServiceTitan goes full enterprise at $200-300+ per user.</p>

<p>The choice between these platforms often comes down to your growth trajectory and operational complexity. Companies with 10-30 technicians doing residential and light commercial work typically find FieldEdge sufficient. Shops with 30+ techs, complex commercial contracts, or aggressive expansion plans usually need ServiceTitan's deeper feature set.</p>

<p>For context, our analysis of HVAC software adoption shows that companies spending $4,000-8,000 monthly on software typically have 20-40 field employees. This puts both FieldEdge and ServiceTitan in direct competition for the same customer segment.</p>

</div>

<div class="prose max-w-none">

