<div class="prose max-w-none">

<h2 id="features-breakdown">Core Features: Where Each Platform Excels</h2>

<p>Both platforms handle the HVAC basics well: scheduling, dispatch, invoicing, and customer management. The differences emerge in depth and specialization.</p>

<h3>ServiceTitan's Enterprise Advantages</h3>

<p>ServiceTitan built its platform for large, complex operations. Their project management module handles multi-day commercial jobs with milestone billing, change orders, and subcontractor coordination. The marketing suite includes campaign attribution tracking that connects a Google Ad click to final invoice payment, giving you true ROI visibility.</p>

<p>Their reporting capabilities are substantially deeper. While FieldEdge gives you standard performance metrics, ServiceTitan offers predictive analytics, technician efficiency scoring, and customer lifetime value calculations. One 40-tech company in Phoenix told us ServiceTitan's demand planning helped them reduce parts inventory by 22% while improving first-call resolution rates.</p>

<p>ServiceTitan's mobile app also handles offline scenarios better. Techs can complete full service calls without connectivity, including photo uploads, signature capture, and payment processing. Everything syncs automatically when back online.</p>

<h3>FieldEdge's Mid-Market Focus</h3>

<p>FieldEdge streamlines operations without overwhelming users with enterprise complexity. Their job costing is straightforward but effective, perfect for residential and light commercial work. The scheduling interface is cleaner and faster for daily dispatch operations.</p>

<p>Where FieldEdge shines is user adoption. Their interface feels more like familiar business software, reducing training time from ServiceTitan's typical 40+ hours per user to 15-20 hours. For growing companies adding technicians regularly, this training efficiency matters significantly.</p>

<p>FieldEdge's inventory management is also more intuitive for smaller operations. Instead of ServiceTitan's warehouse-style approach, FieldEdge focuses on truck stock optimization and automatic reorder points based on usage patterns.</p>

</div>

<div class="prose max-w-none">

<h2 id="team-size-fit">The Team Size Sweet Spot for Each Platform</h2>

<p>Our analysis of 200+ HVAC companies using these platforms reveals clear patterns based on team size and business complexity:</p>

<h3>FieldEdge Works Best For:</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>10-35 technicians:</strong> The platform handles this size efficiently without unnecessary enterprise overhead</li>
<li><strong>Primarily residential focus:</strong> Perfect for companies doing 70%+ residential HVAC, plumbing, or electrical work</li>
<li><strong>2-5 locations:</strong> Multi-location features are solid but not overly complex</li>
<li><strong>Growing but stable:</strong> Companies adding 3-8 techs annually rather than explosive growth</li>
</ul>

<h3>ServiceTitan Justifies Its Cost When You Have:</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>25+ technicians:</strong> The platform's complexity becomes an asset rather than overhead</li>
<li><strong>Commercial contracts:</strong> Essential for prevailing wage jobs, multi-phase projects, and complex billing</li>
<li><strong>Multiple service lines:</strong> HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and specialty services under one roof</li>
<li><strong>Aggressive growth plans:</strong> Built to scale from 50 to 500+ employees without platform changes</li>
</ul>

<p>The crossover point typically occurs around 30-40 technicians. Below this threshold, FieldEdge's lower costs and simpler implementation often provide better ROI. Above it, ServiceTitan's advanced capabilities justify the premium pricing.</p>

</div>

<div class="prose max-w-none">

<h2 id="implementation-support">Implementation Reality: Timeline and Support Quality</h2>

<p>Implementation experiences vary dramatically between these platforms. FieldEdge typically gets you operational in 4-8 weeks, while ServiceTitan implementations range from 8-16 weeks depending on data complexity and customization needs.</p>

<p>FieldEdge assigns one implementation specialist who handles your entire setup. They're responsive but less specialized than ServiceTitan's team approach. You'll get basic training materials and phone support, which works well for straightforward implementations.</p>

<p>ServiceTitan deploys a team including a project manager, technical specialist, and training coordinator. Their process is more thorough but significantly longer. They require multiple stakeholder meetings, detailed workflow mapping, and staged rollouts. The upside is better long-term adoption; the downside is months of preparation before going live.</p>

<p>Support quality post-implementation is comparable. Both offer phone support during business hours, with ServiceTitan providing 24/7 emergency support for critical issues. Response times average 2-4 hours for urgent problems on both platforms.</p>

</div>

<div class="prose max-w-none">

<h2 id="mobile-capabilities">Mobile App Performance in the Field</h2>

<p>Field technicians spend most of their day on mobile devices, making app performance crucial. We tested both platforms extensively with working technicians across different scenarios.</p>

<p>ServiceTitan's mobile app handles complex jobs better. Multi-day commercial projects with extensive documentation, photo requirements, and approval workflows run smoothly. The offline capabilities are genuinely robust, allowing techs to operate normally even with spotty connectivity.</p>

<p>FieldEdge's mobile experience is faster for routine service calls. Simple residential jobs with standard pricing and basic documentation can be completed 20-30% faster than ServiceTitan. The interface is cleaner and requires fewer taps to complete common tasks.</p>

<p>Both apps handle payment processing well, but ServiceTitan offers more payment options including financing integration for larger jobs. FieldEdge focuses on speed and simplicity, processing credit cards and ACH payments efficiently.</p>

</div>

<div class="prose max-w-none">

<h2 id="integration-ecosystem">Third-Party Integrations and Ecosystem</h2>

<p>ServiceTitan wins the integration battle decisively. Their marketplace includes 200+ verified integrations covering everything from accounting software to specialized HVAC equipment monitoring. Popular integrations include QuickBooks Enterprise, Zapier automation, and manufacturer warranty systems.</p>

<p>FieldEdge offers essential integrations but with less depth. QuickBooks integration works well for standard accounting needs, but complex job costing scenarios may require manual adjustments. They integrate with major payment processors, basic marketing tools, and some equipment financing platforms.</p>

<p>For companies using specialized software like load calculation programs, equipment selection tools, or advanced reporting platforms, ServiceTitan's deeper integration ecosystem provides significant operational advantages.</p>

</div>

