<h2 id="verdict">Final Verdict: Matching Platform to Business Stage</h2>

<p>The FieldEdge vs ServiceTitan decision ultimately depends on where your HVAC company sits today and where you're headed in the next 3-5 years.</p>

<p><strong>Choose FieldEdge if you:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Have 10-35 technicians with steady, predictable growth</li>
<li>Focus primarily on residential and light commercial work</li>
<li>Want faster implementation and user adoption</li>
<li>Need to control software costs while maintaining functionality</li>
<li>Value simplicity and ease of use over advanced features</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Choose ServiceTitan if you:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Have 25+ technicians or plan to reach this size within two years</li>
<li>Handle significant commercial contracts or complex projects</li>
<li>Need advanced reporting, analytics, and business intelligence</li>
<li>Plan aggressive expansion or multiple service line additions</li>
<li>Can justify premium pricing with measurable ROI improvements</li>
</ul>

<p>Both platforms will handle basic HVAC operations effectively. The decision comes down to matching platform capabilities to your business complexity and growth trajectory. Companies that choose correctly see 15-25% improvements in operational efficiency within the first year.</p>

